trans-unit.source: Multiclass Decision Jungle

trans-unit.source: Creates a multiclass classification model using the decision jungle algorithm
trans-unit.target: Creates a multiclass classification model using the decision jungle algorithm

trans-unit.source: Module Overview
trans-unit.target: Module Overview

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Multiclass Decision Jungle</ui> module to create a machine learning model that is based on a supervised learning algorithm called <newTerm>decision jungles</newTerm>.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Multiclass Decision Jungle</ui> module to create a machine learning model that is based on a supervised learning algorithm called <newTerm>decision jungles</newTerm>.

trans-unit.source: The model can be used to predict a target that has multiple values.
trans-unit.target: The model can be used to predict a target that has multiple values.

trans-unit.source: The module returns an untrained classification model that can be passed to the <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> module for training on a labeled training data set.
trans-unit.target: The module returns an untrained classification model that can be passed to the <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> module for training on a labeled training data set.

trans-unit.source: The trained model can then be used to make predictions.
trans-unit.target: The trained model can then be used to make predictions.

trans-unit.source: Alternatively, the untrained model can be passed to <link xlink:href="927d65ac-3b50-4694-9903-20f6c1672089" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross Validate Model</link> for cross-validation against a labeled data set.
trans-unit.target: Alternatively, the untrained model can be passed to <link xlink:href="927d65ac-3b50-4694-9903-20f6c1672089" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross Validate Model</link> for cross-validation against a labeled data set.

trans-unit.source: Understanding Decision Jungles
trans-unit.target: Understanding Decision Jungles

trans-unit.source: <externalLink><linkText>Decision jungles</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=403675</linkUri></externalLink> are a recent extension to <externalLink><linkText>decision forests</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=403677</linkUri></externalLink>.
trans-unit.target: <externalLink><linkText>Decision jungles</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=403675</linkUri></externalLink> are a recent extension to <externalLink><linkText>decision forests</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=403677</linkUri></externalLink>.

trans-unit.source: A decision jungle consists of an ensemble of decision directed acyclic graphs (DAGs).
trans-unit.target: A decision jungle consists of an ensemble of decision directed acyclic graphs (DAGs).

trans-unit.source: Decision jungles have the following advantages:
trans-unit.target: Decision jungles have the following advantages:

trans-unit.source: By allowing tree branches to merge, a decision DAG typically has a lower memory footprint and a better generalization performance than a decision tree, albeit at the cost of a somewhat higher training time.
trans-unit.target: By allowing tree branches to merge, a decision DAG typically has a lower memory footprint and a better generalization performance than a decision tree, albeit at the cost of a somewhat higher training time.

trans-unit.source: Decision jungles are non-parametric models, which can represent non-linear decision boundaries.
trans-unit.target: Decision jungles are non-parametric models, which can represent non-linear decision boundaries.

trans-unit.source: They perform integrated feature selection and classification and are resilient in the presence of noisy features.
trans-unit.target: They perform integrated feature selection and classification and are resilient in the presence of noisy features.

trans-unit.source: How to Configure a Decision Jungle Model
trans-unit.target: How to Configure a Decision Jungle Model

trans-unit.source: This module supports customization using the following options:
trans-unit.target: This module supports customization using the following options:

trans-unit.source: Drag the <ui>Multiclass Decision</ui> Forest module into your experiment.
trans-unit.target: Drag the <ui>Multiclass Decision</ui> Forest module into your experiment.

trans-unit.source: Set model <legacyLink xlink:href="#bkmk_Options" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">options</legacyLink>.
trans-unit.target: Set model <legacyLink xlink:href="#bkmk_Options" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">options</legacyLink>.

trans-unit.source: Connect an instance of <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> to train the model using a tagged dataset.
trans-unit.target: Connect an instance of <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> to train the model using a tagged dataset.

trans-unit.source: <newTerm>Tagged</newTerm> means that the dataset contains a label column that contains exactly two outcomes.
trans-unit.target: <newTerm>Tagged</newTerm> means that the dataset contains a label column that contains exactly two outcomes.

trans-unit.source: The trained model can then be used to make predictions.
trans-unit.target: The trained model can then be used to make predictions.

trans-unit.source: Alternatively, the untrained model can be passed to <link xlink:href="75fb875d-6b86-4d46-8bcc-74261ade5826" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross Validate Model</link> for cross-validation against a labeled data set.
trans-unit.target: Alternatively, the untrained model can be passed to <link xlink:href="75fb875d-6b86-4d46-8bcc-74261ade5826" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross Validate Model</link> for cross-validation against a labeled data set.

trans-unit.source: Options
trans-unit.target: Options

trans-unit.source: This module supports extensive customization of the decision jungle model using these parameters:
trans-unit.target: This module supports extensive customization of the decision jungle model using these parameters:

trans-unit.source: Resampling method
trans-unit.target: Resampling method

trans-unit.source: Specify which method should be used to bootstrap the graph creation.
trans-unit.target: Specify which method should be used to bootstrap the graph creation.

trans-unit.source: <ui>Bagging</ui>.
trans-unit.target: <ui>Bagging</ui>.

trans-unit.source: Select this option to use bagging, also called bootstrap aggregating.
trans-unit.target: Select this option to use bagging, also called bootstrap aggregating.

trans-unit.source: Each tree in a decision forest outputs a Gaussian distribution by way of prediction.
trans-unit.target: Each tree in a decision forest outputs a Gaussian distribution by way of prediction.

trans-unit.source: The aggregation is to find a Gaussian whose first two moments match the moments of the mixture of Gaussians given by combining all Gaussians returned by individual trees.
trans-unit.target: The aggregation is to find a Gaussian whose first two moments match the moments of the mixture of Gaussians given by combining all Gaussians returned by individual trees.

trans-unit.source: <ui>Replicate</ui>.
trans-unit.target: <ui>Replicate</ui>.

trans-unit.source: In replication, each tree is trained on exactly the same input data.
trans-unit.target: In replication, each tree is trained on exactly the same input data.

trans-unit.target: Number of optimization steps per decision DAG layer

trans-unit.source: Type a value that defines the number of iterations used when building each decision DAG.
trans-unit.target: Type a value that defines the number of iterations used when building each decision DAG.

trans-unit.source: Allow unknown values for categorical features
trans-unit.target: Allow unknown values for categorical features

trans-unit.source: Select this option to create a group for unknown values in testing or validation data.
trans-unit.target: Select this option to create a group for unknown values in testing or validation data.

trans-unit.source: If you deselect it, the model can accept only the values that are contained in the training data.
trans-unit.target: If you deselect it, the model can accept only the values that are contained in the training data.

trans-unit.source: In the former case, the model might be less precise for known values, but it can provide better predictions for new (unknown) values.

trans-unit.source: Recommendations
trans-unit.target: Recommendations

trans-unit.source: If you have limited data or want to minimize the time spent training the model, try these settings:
trans-unit.target: If you have limited data or want to minimize the time spent training the model, try these settings:

trans-unit.source: <legacyBold>Limited training set.</legacyBold> If the training set contains a limited number of instances:
trans-unit.target: <legacyBold>Limited training set.</legacyBold> If the training set contains a limited number of instances:

trans-unit.source: Create the decision jungle using a large number of decision DAGs (for example, more than 20)
trans-unit.target: Create the decision jungle using a large number of decision DAGs (for example, more than 20)

trans-unit.source: Use the <ui>Bagging</ui> option for resampling.
trans-unit.target: Use the <ui>Bagging</ui> option for resampling.

trans-unit.source: Specify a large number of optimization steps per DAG layer (for example, more than 10,000).
trans-unit.target: Specify a large number of optimization steps per DAG layer (for example, more than 10,000).

trans-unit.source: <legacyBold>Limited training time.</legacyBold> If the training set contains a large number of instances and training time is limited:
trans-unit.target: <legacyBold>Limited training time.</legacyBold> If the training set contains a large number of instances and training time is limited:

trans-unit.source: Create the decision jungle that uses a smaller number of decision DAGs (for example, 5-10).
trans-unit.target: Create the decision jungle that uses a smaller number of decision DAGs (for example, 5-10).

trans-unit.source: Use the <ui>Replicate</ui> option for resampling.
trans-unit.target: Use the <ui>Replicate</ui> option for resampling.

trans-unit.source: Specify a smaller number of optimization steps per DAG layer (for example, less than 2000).
